Exceptions 

1) JVM Exception (JVM Raises Exception when particular situation occurs)
2) Programming Exception(Programmer throws some exception depending on buisness requirement or API exception)


JVM
- ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException(U)
- NullPointerException(U)
- ClassCastException(U)
- StackOverflowError(U)
- NoClassDefFoundError(U)
- ExceptionInInitializerError(U)   -> Exception in executing static variable assignment or static block static int a=10/0


Programatic (Programmer or Api Developer raises)
- IllegalArgumentException(U)    thread.setPriority(18)
	- NumberFormatException(U)	Integer.parseInt("ten")
- IllegalStateException(U)	(call a method at wrong time)
	-IllegalThreadStateException	thread.start(); thread.start();

- AssertionError(U)	asser(x>10) x not gt 10 then AssertionError



